Aerospace engineering is a field of engineering that specializes in vehicles that move in fluids .
This usually means working with airplanes , cars , boats , trains , or spacecrafts .
To work in Aerospace engineering you must learn a lot .
This is done depending on what you want to do .
Aerospace engineers ( those who design and oversee repair of vehicles ) study at a university or college and must earn a degree .
Technicians ( those who repair and construct vehicles ) will do a shorter course and ` on the job ' training .
Aerospace jobs include astronauts , pilots , and other professionals .
